  "text": "Affiliation and achievement motives are important for the psychological and social well-being of young adults [CITATION_1] . Achievement motivation is an important issue for psychologists of religion because it has been correlated with personality traits and religiosity [CITATION_2] . Moreover, gender differences in achievement motivation have been studied widely in the context of academic achievement (13) because gender differences in motivation have been found to predict adolescents' differences in academic achievement [CITATION_3] .",
